Sydney Name Meaning in English

What does the name Sydney mean? What is the meaning of the name Sydney, lucky number, lucky stone, origin and religion.

Origin of the name Sydney: Transferred use of the surname originating as a Norman baronial name taken from the place-name St. Denis in Normandy. Alternatively, the name arose independently in England and is derived from the Old English elements sīd (extensive, wide) and ieg (island in a river, riverside meadow).

Sydney Name Meaning, Origin & Details

Meaning: Of the wide meadow Short Info: The Australian city of Sydney has a population of over 4 million and is the most populated city in the country. Details: This name of Old English origin means "wide meadow". Also possibly derived from the Norman French place name Saint Denis. Gender: For both boy and girl, unisex, transgender, neutral gender Origin: English Religion: Christian Suitable for: Unisex / Gender neutral Hardness: Medium hard to pronounce Uniqueness: It is a common name Short & Easy: Not very short Syllables: 6 Letters and 1 Words
